---
title: "Sequence Diagram: /update-docs Skill"
---
%%{init: {'theme': 'neutral'}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    actor User
    participant Claude
    participant Status as /status
    participant Validate as /validate-claude-docs
    participant FS as File System
    participant Glob as Glob Tool

    User->>Claude: /update-docs <project-path> [mode]

    note over Claude: Capture start timestamp<br/>(used by Report phase for wall_clock_sec)
    Claude->>Claude: START_TS = date +%s<br/>RUN_TS = date -u +%Y%m%dT%H%M%SZ<br/>DISPLAY_TS = date +%Y%m%d-%H%M%S

    note over Claude: Preflight<br/>follow api-skill-preflight

    note over Claude,Status: Phase: Inventory — delegate
    Claude->>Status: run /status <project-path>
    Status-->>Claude: stats, coverage,<br/>staleness, issue hints

    note over Claude,Validate: Phase: Validate — delegate
    alt mode = report
        Claude->>Validate: run /validate-claude-docs <path><br/>(no fix)
    else
        Claude->>Validate: run /validate-claude-docs <path> fix
    end
    Validate-->>Claude: issues + trivial fixes applied

    note over Claude,Glob: Phase: Detect drift (unique)
    Claude->>Glob: re-scan stack markers,<br/>module list, paths: globs,<br/>@path imports
    Glob-->>Claude: current code state
    Claude->>FS: read CLAUDE.md sections,<br/>module CLAUDE.md, rule frontmatter
    FS-->>Claude: documented state
    Claude->>Claude: diff → drift list<br/>(stack / modules / paths / imports / commands)

    note over Claude: Phase: Build update plan (unique)
    Claude->>Claude: classify drift items<br/>safe-auto / needs-review / destructive

    alt mode not specified
        Claude->>User: Drift found — how to proceed?<br/>[1] Interactive — review each change   (default)<br/>[2] Auto — apply safe changes, confirm risky<br/>[3] Report only — no writes, just show plan
        User->>Claude: choice
    end

    alt mode = report
        Claude->>User: show plan, no writes
    else mode = auto
        Claude->>Claude: apply safe, prompt on review + destructive
    else interactive (default)
        Claude->>User: Plan box with drift items grouped by risk:<br/>  Safe (auto):  N items<br/>  Review needed: N items<br/>  Destructive:  N items<br/>[1] Apply all safe + review each risky<br/>[2] Apply safe only, skip risky<br/>[3] Select individual items
        User->>Claude: choice
    end

    note over Claude,FS: Phase: Apply drift updates (unique)
    opt Stack / build commands drifted
        Claude->>FS: refresh Build & Run in CLAUDE.md
    end
    opt Directory tree drifted
        Claude->>FS: refresh Project Structure
    end
    opt New modules
        Claude->>FS: create module CLAUDE.md
    end
    opt Removed modules (approved)
        Claude->>FS: delete orphan module CLAUDE.md
    end
    opt Rule paths: globs broken
        Claude->>FS: rewrite paths: or flag for review
    end
    opt Dead @path imports
        Claude->>FS: remove broken imports
    end

    note over Claude,Validate: Phase: Verify — delegate
    Claude->>Validate: run /validate-claude-docs <path><br/>(no fix — just confirm clean)
    Validate-->>Claude: post-state report

    note over Claude,FS: Phase: Report (unique) — write file + show dashboard
    Claude->>Claude: END_TS = date +%s<br/>wall_clock_sec = END_TS - START_TS
    Claude->>FS: Collect artefact list<br/>(created / modified / deleted with wc -l)
    FS-->>Claude: Paths + line counts
    Claude->>FS: Write .claude/state/reports/<br/>update-docs-DISPLAY_TS.md<br/>(per rules/report-format.md —<br/>first line machine-diff comment,<br/>body with Summary / Phase Timings /<br/>Drift kinds / Artefacts / Next-step)
    FS-->>Claude: Report saved

    Claude->>User: update report dashboard<br/>[FIX] / [UPDATED] / [SKIPPED]<br/>+ wall_clock_sec<br/>+ saved report path<br/>+ next steps
